## What NOT to Do

- Do not introduce colors outside the palette above. Stick to primary / accent / background / text / muted / success / danger.
- Do not use stock syntax themes (vitesse-dark, github-dark, etc.) for code blocks. Code uses the brand-derived shiki theme generated from this palette.
- Do not use generic fade-to-black transitions. Match-cut on the signature motif or use a brand-primary directional sweep.
- Do not place ambient decorations within ~100px of focal elements; keep them at ≤0.5 opacity.
- Do not stack peer content with gaps outside the 40–56px band; keep title→content gaps in the 72–80px band.
